.TH CSVVIEW 1 "2026-03-12" "csvview 12" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
csvview \- fast terminal CSV viewer and editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B csvview
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIfile\fR
.br
.B csvview
.BR \-\-cat
[\fB\-\-column=\fINAME\fR] [\fB\-\-output=\fIFILE\fR] \fIfile1\fR \fIfile2\fR ...
.br
.B csvview
.BR \-\-split
.B \-\-by=\fICOLUMN\fR
[\fB\-\-output\-dir=\fIDIR\fR] [\fB\-\-drop\-col\fR] \fIfile\fR
.br
.B csvview
(no arguments \(em opens recent file picker)
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B csvview
is a terminal-based CSV viewer and editor built with ncurses.
It supports filtering, sorting, pivot tables, graphs, computed columns,
column statistics, and more \(em with no external dependencies beyond ncurses.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-sep= CHAR
Use \fICHAR\fR as the field delimiter. Examples: \fB\-\-sep=\\t\fR (TSV),
\fB\-\-sep=;\fR, \fB\-\-sep=|\fR.
File extension is auto-detected: \fI.csv\fR\(->comma, \fI.tsv\fR\(->tab, \fI.psv\fR\(->pipe.
.TP
.B \-\-cat
Concatenate multiple CSV files into one, adding a column with the source filename.
.TP
.BI \-\-column= NAME
Column name for the source filename in \fB\-\-cat\fR mode (default: \fIsource_file\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-output= FILE
Output filename for \fB\-\-cat\fR mode (default: \fImerged_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.csv\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-split
Split a CSV file into multiple files, one per unique value of a column.
.TP
.BI \-\-by= COLUMN
Column to split by (required with \fB\-\-split\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-output\-dir= DIR
Directory for split output files (created if needed).
.TP
.B \-\-drop\-col
Remove the split column from all output files.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-? ", " \-\-help ", " /h
Show help and exit.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.SS Main view
.TP
.B Arrows / hjkl
Move cursor
.TP
.B PageUp / PageDown
Scroll one page
.TP
.B Home / End
First / last visible row
.TP
.B /
Start simple search
.TP
.B n / N
Next / previous search result
.TP
.B f
Quick filter
.TP
.B Shift+F
Advanced filter
.TP
.B Enter
Edit current cell
.TP
.B s
Save file
.TP
.B t
Column settings
.TP
.B w / W
Increase / decrease column width
.TP
.B A
Auto-fit current column width
.TP
.B [ / ]
Sort ascending / descending
.TP
.B r / R
Reset sorting
.TP
.B Ctrl+R
Reload file (keeps filters and sort)
.TP
.B z
Freeze / unfreeze columns up to current
.TP
.B d / D
Column statistics
.TP
.B p / P
Pivot table
.TP
.B g / G
Graph for current column
.TP
.B q / Esc
Quit
.TP
.B ?
Show help
.SS Command mode (press \fB:\fR)
.TP
.BI :e " [file]"
Export current view to CSV
.TP
.BI :dr " N"
Delete row N (1-based)
.TP
.BI :cr " name"
Rename current column
.TP
.BI :cal " [name]"
Add column to the left
.TP
.BI :car " [name]"
Add column to the right
.TP
.BI :cf " formula"
Fill / compute column by formula
.TP
.BI :cd " name"
Delete column
.TP
.BI :fz " N"
Freeze first N columns
.TP
.B :fs
Save current filter
.TP
.B :fl
Open saved filters list
.SH FILTER SYNTAX
Filters support: \fB= != > >= < <=\fR, \fBAND\fR, \fBOR\fR, \fB!\fR (NOT).
.PP
Examples:
.RS
total > 500
.br
total >= 100 AND status = paid
.br
date >= 2026-01
.RE
.PP
For dates: \fB= 2026-01\fR matches all rows in January 2026.
.SH COMPUTED COLUMNS
Activated with \fB:cf <expression>\fR on the current column.
.PP
Operators: \fB+ \- * / ( )\fR
.br
Functions: \fBround\fR, \fBabs\fR, \fBfloor\fR, \fBceil\fR, \fBmod\fR, \fBpow\fR, \fBif\fR, \fBempty\fR
.br
Aggregates (filtered rows): \fBcol_sum\fR, \fBcol_avg\fR, \fBcol_min\fR, \fBcol_max\fR,
\fBcol_count\fR, \fBcol_median\fR, \fBcol_percentile\fR, \fBcol_stddev\fR, \fBcol_var\fR,
\fBcol_rank\fR, \fBcol_pct\fR
.br
Aggregates (whole file): same names with \fB_all\fR suffix
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.csvview_history
Recent files list (max 20 entries). Opened automatically when csvview is run with no arguments.
.TP
.I file.csvf
Per-file settings: column types, formats, widths, hidden columns, freeze count, saved filters.
.TP
.I file.pivot
Saved pivot table settings for the file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Open a CSV file:
.B csvview data.csv
.TP
Open a TSV file:
.B csvview data.tsv
.TP
Open with semicolon delimiter:
.B csvview \-\-sep=; data.csv
.TP
Merge files with source column:
.B csvview \-\-cat \-\-column=source \-\-output=merged.csv jan.csv feb.csv mar.csv
.TP
Split by region column:
.B csvview \-\-split \-\-by=region \-\-output-dir=splits data.csv
